    {
      "content": "<p>At right are three greyscale images obtained using red, green, and blue filters. Notice in each image where it is dark and where it is bright. A color (red, green, or blue) is then assigned to each of the filtered greyscale images. This is known as colorizing the image. Finally, the three <a href='https://rubinobservatory.org/for-educators/glossary/colorize' target='_blank'>colorized</a> images are combined to create the full color image shown on the right.</p><p>Compare the filtered images to the full color image, then choose the right words to finish the following sentences.</p>",
